<!DOCTYPE html>
<!-- EXERCISE: Set the language of the document to English using the 'lang' attribute on the opening html tag below. -->
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <!-- EXERCISE: Add a meta tag below to specify the character encoding for the document as UTF-8. -->
    <meta charset="UTF-8">

    <!-- EXERCISE: Add a meta tag for responsive design. It should set the viewport's width to the device-width and the initial zoom level to 1.0. -->
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">

    <!-- EXERCISE: Add a title for the page below. It should say "About [Your Name]". This text will appear in the browser tab. -->
    
    <title> about wesam</title>
  </head>
  <body>

    <!--
      Welcome, students!
      Your task is to replace the comments in this file with the correct HTML tags.
      Fill in the content with your own personal information.
    -->

    <!-- EXERCISE: Use the <h1> tag to create the main heading of the page. The content should be your full name. -->
    <h1>wesam abdurabu masharh</h1>

    <!-- EXERCISE: Add a horizontal rule (<hr>) tag below to create a line separator. -->
    
     <hr>
    <!-- EXERCISE: Use an <h2> tag to create a sub-heading that says "My Introduction". -->
     <h2>My Introduction</h2>

    <!-- EXERCISE: Use a <p> (paragraph) tag to write a short introduction about yourself. -->
    <p> Hello, my name is Wesam Masharh. I'm a software engineering student at the University of Bahrain (UOB).
    <!-- EXERCISE: Use an <h2> tag to create a sub-heading that says "My Hobbies". -->
    <h2>My Hobbies</h2>

    <!-- 
      EXERCISE: Create an unordered list (<ul>) below to list your hobbies.
      Inside the list, each hobby should be a separate list item (<li>).
      Please add at least three hobbies.
    -->
      <ul>
  <li>Running</li>
  <li>Exercising / working out</li>
  <li>Playing video games</li>
      </ul>
    

    <!-- EXERCISE: Use an <h2> tag to create a sub-heading that says "Favorite Quote". -->

    <h2>Favorite Quote</h2>
    <!--
      EXERCISE: Use the <blockquote> tag to display your favorite quote.
      Inside the blockquote, use a <p> tag for the quote itself.
      After the quote, use a <cite> tag for the author of the quote.
    -->
    <blockquote>
  <p>
    Fear does not prevent death, but it prevents life..
  </p>
  <cite>—Naguib Mahfouz.</cite>
</blockquote>

    <!-- EXERCISE: Use an <h2> tag for a section called "Find Me Online". -->

      <h2>Find Me Online</h2>

    <!--
      EXERCISE: Create a hyperlink (<a> tag) that links to your favorite website.
      The 'href' attribute should contain the full URL (e.g., "https://www.google.com/").
      The text inside the tag should be the name of the website, for example, "Link to Google".
      Bonus: Add the 'target="_blank"' attribute to make the link open in a new tab.
    -->

    <a href="https://www.youtube.com/" target="_blank">YouTube</a>

    <!--
      BONUS EXERCISE: Add an image of something you like.
      Use the <img> tag.
      You will need to find an image URL online to use for the 'src' attribute.
      Don't forget to add a descriptive 'alt' attribute for accessibility!
    -->
     <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1516414925501-860ef818b814?auto=format&fit=crop&w=600&q=80" 
     alt="A close-up shot of a classic vintage typewriter with circular keys" 
     width="500">
  </body>
</html>
